      <descriptions>
        <description xml:lang="en-us" descriptionType="Abstract">Longterm meteorological and snow station on a steep (c. 40 degrees) North-East exposed slope at 2090 m a.s.l above  Davos, Switzerland. Established 1975 and ongoing measurements made, although instruments have changed during this period. The station is located within a experimental plantation that serves as avalanche protection to downslope communities as well as a unique site for treeline dynamics research.</description>
